As a ex-kemingnite, it's honestly a school that provides a well learning experience, the teachers arent bias at all, the school really trys their best to be well rounded, love the fun activities they plan like "arts 4 you", " play at recess" these small gestures rlly do help make your 6 years there meaningful, when i graduated in 2023 we were planned a heart warming, senior lunch graduation party , the planning was great overall I lob the school , I would honestly do anything to go back, keep up the good work kmps

forever a kemingnite
School is ok. Food and sanitation can be improved. Very nice noodle, Malay and cooked food stalls. Teachers are nice.

Volume of Teachers speaking into the mic in the hall is very loud, it's very disturbing. Please lower the volume. Also the teachers need to be mindful that the residents can hear them calling out certain students repeatedly and harshly. Like stepmother scolding the stepkids la.
The teachers are very biased but canteen food is great
